toolbar and choose $gui(By Name), $gui(By Size), $gui(By
Type), $gui(By Modification Date), or $gui(By Access
Date).

As an example, if you select $gui(By Name), the files will be sorted
by their names, in alphabetical order. See $link[>#ways] for other
options.

You can sort in the reverse order by selecting $gui(Reversed Order)
from the menu.


== List view
   [#list-view]

To sort files in a different order, click one of the column headings in
the file manager. For example, click $gui(Type) to sort by file type.
Click the column heading again to sort in the reverse order.

In list view, you can show columns with more attributes and sort on those
columns. Click the view options button in the toolbar, pick $gui(Visible
