Columnsâ€¦) and select the columns that you want to be visible. You will
then be able to sort by those columns. See $link[>nautilus-list] for
descriptions of available columns.


== Ways of sorting files
   [#ways]

[terms]
- Name
* Sorts alphabetically by the name of the file.

- Size
* Sorts by the size of the file (how much disk space it takes up). Sorts
  from smallest to largest by default.

- Type
* Sorts alphabetically by the file type. Files of the same type are
  grouped together, then sorted by name.

- Last Modified
* Sorts by the date and time that a file was last changed. Sorts from
  oldest to newest by default.

[comment]
Mention that it is possible to reverse the sort order with the $gui(Reverse
Order) option.
